TITLE: No charges for Detroit-area cop who shot armed suspect in police station lobby
SUMMARY: A Dearborn, Michigan police officer will not be charged for killing Ali Naji, who entered a police station lobby in December and attempted to shoot him.

TITLE: Los Angelenos are fleeing public transportation amid violence, open drug-use spike: 'Horror'
SUMMARY: Public transportation in Los Angeles is seeing a spike in violence and open drug use, which is keeping other riders away from the subway, according to recent reports.

TITLE: Investigation underway after AI tool may have misinterpreted a childâ€™s disability as parental neglect
SUMMARY: The U.S. child welfare system is under investigation for using an artificial intelligence tool that may have discriminated against people with disabilities.

TITLE: US Army parachute team member dies in training accident in Florida
SUMMARY: The United States Army is remembering a member of the parachute team who died after sustaining injuries during a training jump in Florida earlier this week.

TITLE: 5 employees at high-end NJ mall revived after suspected fentanyl overdoses
SUMMARY: Police in Hackensack, New Jersey, are investigating the source of the suspected fentanyl after five workers at The Shops at Riverside mall appeared to have overdosed.

TITLE: Two arrested in connection with deadly Florida surf shop shooting: police
SUMMARY: Two men are in custody after a man was shot and killed inside a surf shop in Clearwater, Florida, earlier this week, police say.

TITLE: Flood warning in Sedona, Arizona, downgraded hours after issuing evacuation alerts
SUMMARY: Hours after telling residents to evacuate immediately, a flood warning for the city of Sedona, Arizona, has been downgraded to an advisory.

TITLE: Black mental patient pinned down, smothered to death by deputies at Virginia hospital, prosecutor says
SUMMARY: A Black man who was handcuffed and shackled was smothered to death as he was getting admitted to a mental hospital in Virginia. Seven deputies were charged in the killing.

TITLE: Wisconsin Republican lawmakers circulate bill that would designate an official state rifle
SUMMARY: Lawmakers in Wisconsin have proposed a bill to designate an official state rifle. The bill proposes that the Henry All-Weather .45-70 become the official rifle of Wisconsin.

TITLE: Ex-Detroit police officer sentenced to over 2 years for role in bribery case involving towing company
SUMMARY: Former police officer Daniel Vickers was sentenced to over two years in prison for his role in a towing bribery scheme. Vickers accepted money in exchange for towing service referrals.

TITLE: Texas man whose son helped dump mother's corpse convicted of killing wife, lover after catching them on camera
SUMMARY: Jordy Husein Suljanovic was convicted of killing his wife and her lover in Texas, and Suljanovic's son, Jordy Suljanovic Jr., helped his father dispose of her body.

TITLE: Dallas nightclub shooting leaves 2 dead, 1 injured
SUMMARY: Two people are dead and one is injured after a shooting at Dallas nightclub in the Deep Ellum area. Authorities are still searching for the suspect.

TITLE: Attorney generals in some states refuse to release advisory opinions, while others post dozens each year
SUMMARY: Attorney generals in about 20 percent of the states in the U.S. haven't posted any general opinions in the past few years, while other states post dozens each year.

TITLE: 2 Michigan men convicted of fatally shooting 2 women who were unloading groceries outside their apartment
SUMMARY: A jury convicted two men from Michigan of killing two women who were unloading groceries outside their suburban-Detroit apartment. An infant was discovered unharmed in the women's car.

TITLE: Biden approves federal disaster declaration for New Hampshire following damage caused by December storm
SUMMARY: A severe winter storm in New Hampshire downed trees and power lines causing numerous power outages in December. Biden officially declared a federal disaster declaration on Wednesday.

TITLE: Jared Bridegan murder: Florida state attorney announces arrest in Microsoft exec's slaying
SUMMARY: Authorities announced Thursday that the husband of slain Microsoft executive Jared Bridegan's ex-wife had been arrested for his murder in north Florida more than a year ago.

TITLE: Alabama prison cost estimate jumps by additional $300 million
SUMMARY: The cost estimate of a new 4,000-inmate Alabama prison increased to nearly $1 billion, $300 million more than what was previously authorized.

TITLE: Theft suspect crashes helicopter at Sacramento Executive Airport in California, flees: police
SUMMARY: Police and the FBI in California are searching for a suspect who crashed a helicopter at the Sacramento Executive Airport early Wednesday after attempting to steal the aircraft.

TITLE: 70-year-old man accused of scamming women on dating apps out of $1.8M
SUMMARY: A 70-year-old New York City man is accused of scamming five women out of $1.8 million dollars. Nelson Counne is referred to as the "worst boyfriend on the Upper East Side."

TITLE: Stanford University employee arrested and charged after multiple phony campus rape claims
SUMMARY: Jennifer Ann Gries, a 25-year-old Stanford University employee, was arrested after allegedly fabricating two on-campus rape allegations last year, prosecutors say.

TITLE: 2 men found dead near Utah-Arizona border after canyons flood
SUMMARY: Two men were found dead near the Utah-Arizona border after floodwaters poured into a slot canyon. Several others in the area were rescued in a helicopter.

TITLE: Alex Murdaugh fallout: Mother of Buster Murdaugh's deceased high school classmate seeks independent autopsy
SUMMARY: Stephen Smith's mother, Sandy Smith, is seeking donations for an independent exhumation and autopsy for her son. Smith died in 2015 near the Murdaugh family's hunting estate.

TITLE: Major break in mysterious murder of Florida Microsoft executive Jared Bridegan
SUMMARY: Florida authorities Thursday announced a 'significant development' in the baffling murder of Microsoft executive Jared Bridegan and said more details are forthcoming.

TITLE: Woman locked in closet for 2 months flees her prison; police arrest kidnapping suspect
SUMMARY: Police in Dyersburg, Tennessee, have arrested a man who allegedly held a woman captive in a closet for approximately two months with little access to food and a restroom.

TITLE: Hiker dies on Arches National Park trail in Utah, second death within a month
SUMMARY: Park rangers responded on Sunday to an unresponsive 56-year-old man on Devils Garden Trail at Arches National Park in Utah. The hiker died despite life-saving efforts.
